VR simulation company focused on creating an educational platform for the healthcare industry

18.description:
Sensus 3D is a virtual reality simulation company, focused on the development of 3D sensory experiences.

The purpose of Sensus3D is to reduce the existing border between reality and unreality by generating interaction environments and new contexts of exchange and communication that overcome some of the limitations of space-time dimensions and provide a face-to-face sensitive experience for the user to submerge in the virtual world.

While currently focused on the healthcare industry and surgical training, our dynamic platform easily allows expansion into other use cases and areas of knowledge such as industrial machinery training, company procedures, user education and so on.

Founded by Santiago Racca and Santiago Bestani, Sensus3D brings together some of the best experts in interface design, CGI, photography, 3D animation and VR to disrupt the constantly evolving industry of virtual reality.
